Currently, if we want to search for issues in a particular date only, we would need to construct a JQL with the following:
{code}
created >= <date> AND created <= <date+1>
{code}

Otherwise, the workaround will be query the issues create the day(s) before(may not accurate as it based on the time search):
{code}
created >= "-1d"
{code}

or specify the hours:
{code}
created < "<date> 23:59" and created > "<date> 00:00"
{code}

It would be a great improvement if the date can search directly with the specific date:
{code}
created = <date>
{code}

This would be more intuitive when using the _createdDate_ alias.

